ns.Novel horizons covers the surviving textual material widely, focusing on narrative prose fictions published between 1660 and 1710. In addition to tracing the paratextual poetics of Restoration fiction, this book also covers the state of the art of fiction-writing during the period, discussing character development, narrative point of view and questions of fictionality and realism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCriticism, interpretation, etc. 0aEnglish fictiony17th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictionyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aRestoration literature.  aearly modern fiction.  agenre.  ahistory of the novel.  anovel and romance.  aparatexts.  areader-response criticism.1 aBayer, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610048140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526100481423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526100481/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles